Ran,

255
00:25:43,905 --> 00:25:45,825
why would you say that?

256
00:25:48,065 --> 00:25:49,225
You were dumping a body, weren't you?

257
00:25:52,905 --> 00:25:54,905
Ran, don't scare me.

258
00:25:55,745 --> 00:25:58,145
What… What body?

259
00:25:58,225 --> 00:25:59,705
That sounds scary.

260
00:26:02,705 --> 00:26:04,745
It was Xu Meng and her father.

261
00:26:05,825 --> 00:26:08,425
Xu Meng and her father?
What does that have to do with me?

262
00:26:09,385 --> 00:26:11,785
-Weren't they killed by Wu Shanlong?
-Qiao,

263
00:26:14,465 --> 00:26:15,785
stop lying.

264
00:26:17,265 --> 00:26:20,105
Yao Xincheng, the Bowls dress,

265
00:26:20,185 --> 00:26:21,505
the red heels turned blue,

266
00:26:22,185 --> 00:26:26,465
and what happened in restroom 415,
I've figured it all out.

267
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:32,585
All these years,

268
00:26:33,705 --> 00:26:36,665
how could you act
like nothing happened when facing me

269
00:26:38,505 --> 00:26:39,545
and facing Sir?

270
00:26:41,065 --> 00:26:44,465
You hid it so well, for so long.

271
00:26:45,225 --> 00:26:46,545
I… I didn't…

272
00:26:51,425 --> 00:26:54,105
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

273
00:26:56,545 --> 00:26:58,025
I didn't.

274
00:27:03,105 --> 00:27:04,345
All these years,

275
00:27:07,945 --> 00:27:10,865
I just wanted to crawl
out of the darkness.

276
00:27:11,865 --> 00:27:14,705
I just wanted to feel the sun again.

277
00:27:16,145 --> 00:27:18,345
Why is it so hard?

278
00:27:22,425 --> 00:27:25,625
Ran, tell me.

279
00:27:26,905 --> 00:27:29,145
Why is it so hard?

280
00:27:41,265 --> 00:27:42,385
Qiao,

281
00:27:43,985 --> 00:27:45,105
turn yourself in.

282
00:28:25,225 --> 00:28:28,825
Tomorrow morning, I'll turn myself in.

283
00:28:31,185 --> 00:28:32,185
I'll go with you.

284
00:28:37,185 --> 00:28:39,145
But tonight,

285
00:28:40,145 --> 00:28:41,625
can I stay with you,

286
00:28:42,705 --> 00:28:46,265
with Officer He and Xiaohe,

287
00:28:49,985 --> 00:28:54,985
like a family and have a reunion dinner?

288
00:28:56,385 --> 00:28:59,065
This is my New Year's wish.

289
00:28:59,905 --> 00:29:04,785
It's also been my only wish
all these years.

290
00:29:20,585 --> 00:29:21,585
Eight p.m.

291
00:29:22,865 --> 00:29:23,825
I'll pick you up.

292
00:29:25,785 --> 00:29:27,065
We'll go to Sir's place together.

293
00:29:43,745 --> 00:29:44,985
I'm sorry.

294
00:29:50,065 --> 00:29:51,865
I failed Ran.

295
00:29:55,585 --> 00:29:57,585
If he hadn't come to get me,

296
00:30:00,865 --> 00:30:03,105
he wouldn't have been killed by Xu Meng.

297
00:30:10,265 --> 00:30:11,985
I failed him.

298
00:30:20,505 --> 00:30:21,385
Qiao Suqing,

299
00:30:22,145 --> 00:30:24,385
why do you say it was Xu Meng
who killed Captain Ran?

300
00:30:25,185 --> 00:30:26,305
That afternoon,

301
00:30:28,225 --> 00:30:29,425
I called her

302
00:30:30,625 --> 00:30:32,265
and told her Ran had figured me out.

303
00:30:34,505 --> 00:30:35,665
I told her everything.

304
00:30:36,625 --> 00:30:37,785
What did Xu Meng say?

305
00:30:40,265 --> 00:30:44,265
She said she'd turn herself in with me.

306
00:30:45,905 --> 00:30:46,985
And after that--

307
00:30:47,065 --> 00:30:48,665
So she lied to me!

308
00:30:49,665 --> 00:30:51,305
She lied to me!

309
00:30:52,825 --> 00:30:54,745
She said she was in Kunhai

310
00:30:56,625 --> 00:31:00,025
and would take the earliest train
to Weiyang the next day.

311
00:31:03,545 --> 00:31:04,825
The next morning,

312
00:31:06,665 --> 00:31:08,225
she came to my place.

313
00:31:13,305 --> 00:31:16,545
I even saw her with that day's ticket!

314
00:31:18,465 --> 00:31:20,185
She's a liar!

315
00:31:20,825 --> 00:31:22,105
A liar!

316
00:31:22,745 --> 00:31:25,585
By your account,
Xu Meng had no time to commit it.

317
00:31:31,025 --> 00:31:33,625
It was Xu Meng. She killed Ran.

318
00:31:36,385 --> 00:31:37,945
It had to be her.

319
00:31:51,505 --> 00:31:54,425
CAPTAIN QU
WE'VE GOT HER. INTERROGATION ROOM 2

320
00:32:01,745 --> 00:32:03,265
INTERROGATION ROOM 1

321
00:32:21,225 --> 00:32:26,305
INTERROGATION ROOM 2

322
00:32:36,785 --> 00:32:37,625
<i>Xiaohe.</i>

323
00:33:21,225 --> 00:33:24,105
Don't worry. I've got you.

324
00:34:12,264 --> 00:34:13,425
Xu Meng.

325
00:34:22,585 --> 00:34:24,264
You caught me,

326
00:34:25,264 --> 00:34:27,385
so you must've caught Qiao Suqing too.

327
00:34:28,905 --> 00:34:31,985
Officer, you've got it wrong.

328
00:34:33,425 --> 00:34:35,784
Everything… I did it.

329
00:34:37,385 --> 00:34:39,465
Qiao Suqing had nothing to do with it.

330
00:34:39,545 --> 00:34:43,225
Whether she was involved
is for us to decide.

331
00:34:44,225 --> 00:34:47,665
She's already confessed.
Now it's your turn.

332
00:34:48,264 --> 00:34:51,065
Xu Meng, you faked your death
for 18 years.

333
00:34:51,145 --> 00:34:54,225
We found you and brought you here.

334
00:34:54,304 --> 00:34:56,385
Stop thinking you'll get lucky.

335
00:34:56,465 --> 00:34:58,345
Don't try to protect anyone either.

336
00:34:58,425 --> 00:35:01,105
Tell the truth. It's your only way out.

337
00:35:05,345 --> 00:35:07,025
It's not that I won't talk.

338
00:35:07,625 --> 00:35:09,345
It's just, when I think about it,

339
00:35:11,345 --> 00:35:13,425
there's just too much I've done.

340
00:35:15,905 --> 00:35:18,265
I don't even know where to start.

341
00:35:18,345 --> 00:35:20,145
Then take it one by one.

342
00:35:20,225 --> 00:35:21,385
Start from the beginning!

343
00:35:22,665 --> 00:35:24,145
The first one…

344
00:35:24,745 --> 00:35:25,905
Yao.

345
00:35:26,785 --> 00:35:31,985
It should've been in 1996.

346
00:35:50,345 --> 00:35:51,625
Hello.

347
00:36:33,825 --> 00:36:34,665
Ghost!

348
00:36:50,785 --> 00:36:54,985
<i>I originally just wanted</i>
<i>to teach Yao a lesson,</i>

349
00:36:56,025 --> 00:36:59,705
<i>make him crippled,</i>
<i>so he couldn't abuse Suqing.</i>

350
00:37:00,945 --> 00:37:04,185
<i>I didn't expect he'd actually die.</i>

351
00:37:05,185 --> 00:37:09,505
<i>I watched him stop moving.</i>

352
00:37:12,185 --> 00:37:16,825
<i>I wasn't scared at all.</i>
<i>I actually felt relieved.</i>

353
00:37:18,545 --> 00:37:19,905
<i>Suqing…</i>

354
00:37:21,465 --> 00:37:22,865
<i>She was finally free.</i>

355
00:37:28,025 --> 00:37:29,385
Who else did you kill?

356
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:31,785
Xu Zhihong.

357
00:37:33,305 --> 00:37:34,505
I pushed him.

358
00:37:36,065 --> 00:37:37,385
<i>I watched him die too.</i>

359
00:37:46,465 --> 00:37:47,985
<i>Then I cut up his body</i>

360
00:37:49,185 --> 00:37:50,545
and dumped it in the woods.

361
00:37:51,505 --> 00:37:53,185
Then,

362
00:37:55,785 --> 00:37:57,585
in the summer of 2002,

363
00:37:59,425 --> 00:38:01,625
in Yuanlongli's garage,

364
00:38:02,385 --> 00:38:07,425
I used the same method to set a trap

365
00:38:08,665 --> 00:38:11,065
and killed that sick Wu Shanlong.

366
00:38:11,145 --> 00:38:12,145
Xu Meng,

367
00:38:13,545 --> 00:38:16,745
what we've learned
doesn't match your statement.

368
00:38:17,585 --> 00:38:19,185
Think carefully before you answer.

369
00:38:22,225 --> 00:38:25,985
You mean that Qiao Suqing was involved?

370
00:38:29,265 --> 00:38:32,705
It's been too long.
I don't remember the details.

371
00:38:32,785 --> 00:38:35,665
Either way, I came up with the plans.

372
00:38:36,345 --> 00:38:39,185
I… was the mastermind.

373
00:38:39,265 --> 00:38:43,945
So, using grease at the scene
is your usual method?

374
00:38:45,585 --> 00:38:47,185
Not always.

375
00:38:49,185 --> 00:38:51,385
In winter 2002,

376
00:38:51,465 --> 00:38:53,905
I also set a fire
and burned a child to death.

377
00:38:55,585 --> 00:38:56,745
Be specific.

378
00:38:56,825 --> 00:38:59,585
Where did you set it? Who was the child?

379
00:39:00,745 --> 00:39:03,985
Just… a kid from Yuanlongli.

380
00:39:07,505 --> 00:39:09,145
Back in '97,

381
00:39:10,145 --> 00:39:12,545
he saw me in Yuanlongli.

382
00:39:12,625 --> 00:39:14,265
NEW YORK BLOCK

383
00:39:30,865 --> 00:39:33,305
<i>I ran into him again in 2002.</i>

384
00:39:33,385 --> 00:39:35,465
<i>I thought he recognized me.</i>

385
00:39:35,545 --> 00:39:37,225
<i>He also knew that cop.</i>

386
00:39:37,305 --> 00:39:41,225
<i>Qiao Suqing and I couldn't risk anything.</i>

387
00:39:46,065 --> 00:39:47,145
Fire! Fire!

388
00:39:47,225 --> 00:39:49,105
CAROUSEL'S DEAD HEAT

389
00:39:49,185 --> 00:39:50,465
Fire! Fire!

390
00:39:50,545 --> 00:39:52,625
-Call the police!
-Call the police!

391
00:39:52,705 --> 00:39:54,145
Put it out!

392
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:55,305
Danger!

393
00:39:59,985 --> 00:40:03,065
POLICE

394
00:40:05,825 --> 00:40:07,505
You burned Keyboard to death.

395
00:40:12,145 --> 00:40:15,665
Officer, you knew that boy?

396
00:40:15,745 --> 00:40:17,545
Xu Meng, have you no conscience?

397
00:40:17,625 --> 00:40:19,585
Xiaohe! Xiaohe! Sit down.

398
00:40:20,825 --> 00:40:22,265
Sit down.

399
00:40:23,785 --> 00:40:24,825
Sit down.

400
00:40:30,785 --> 00:40:31,625
Go on.

401
00:40:32,865 --> 00:40:35,345
I didn't mean to kill the boy.

402
00:40:36,025 --> 00:40:38,505
It's just that when
I came back to Weiyang,

403
00:40:39,385 --> 00:40:41,345
I was so angry.

404
00:40:41,905 --> 00:40:44,705
RENTAL AGREEMENT

405
00:41:10,945 --> 00:41:13,665
Why are you here? You didn't even tell me.

406
00:41:14,585 --> 00:41:15,785
When is Yao coming back?

407
00:41:17,345 --> 00:41:20,465
Didn't I say end of the year?
What's wrong?

408
00:41:25,025 --> 00:41:27,625
Sister, our home is ready.

409
00:41:27,705 --> 00:41:29,305
Do you want to go see it with me?

410
00:41:31,465 --> 00:41:34,705
Meng, I… I can't go with you yet.

411
00:41:35,545 --> 00:41:37,745
I have… work. I still need my job.

412
00:41:39,425 --> 00:41:41,105
You must be thirsty.
I'll get you some water.

413
00:41:53,425 --> 00:41:54,905
You're moving?

414
00:41:55,745 --> 00:41:58,385
Didn't you say you'd stay till it's sold?

415
00:42:01,145 --> 00:42:03,265
Well, this place leaks,

416
00:42:03,345 --> 00:42:06,185
and since we're selling it,
I figured I'd move out first.

417
00:42:06,745 --> 00:42:09,825
Closer to work, save on commute.

418
00:42:10,785 --> 00:42:14,025
Then don't rent a place. Come with me.

419
00:42:14,105 --> 00:42:16,825
When Yao gets back, you can come back.

420
00:42:17,625 --> 00:42:20,145
You can find work anywhere, right?

421
00:42:23,785 --> 00:42:27,505
Meng, I think I should wait.

422
00:42:27,585 --> 00:42:31,065
Let's wait a bit longer. Okay?

423
00:42:34,225 --> 00:42:38,065
Sister, what are you waiting for?

424
00:42:38,145 --> 00:42:42,025
Is it this place,
something here you can't leave?

425
00:42:43,505 --> 00:42:44,625
Or is it…

426
00:42:46,705 --> 00:42:48,425
someone you can't let go of?

427
00:42:50,745 --> 00:42:52,185
How could that be?

428
00:42:53,145 --> 00:42:55,065
I just… I already paid three months' rent.

429
00:42:55,145 --> 00:42:57,585
Leaving now would be a waste.

430
00:42:58,785 --> 00:43:00,225
I'm going to the restroom.

431
00:43:47,865 --> 00:43:49,785
<i>For the next few days,</i>

432
00:43:50,465 --> 00:43:52,065
I didn't leave Weiyang.

433
00:43:52,665 --> 00:43:54,385
I just wanted to find out

434
00:43:55,585 --> 00:43:59,945
who the man in those slippers really was.

